# WCL Query Maker API Examples
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@reportCode = ABC123

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### Get Full Report
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}

### Get Report with Specific Fights
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}?fightIDs=1,2,3

### Get Fight Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/fights/1,2

### Get Damage Done Table
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/table/DamageDone?fightIDs=1,2

### Get Healing Table
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/table/Healing?fightIDs=1

### Get Damage Events
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/events/damage/1

### Get Damage Events for Specific Player
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/events/damage/1?sourceID=5

### Get Healing Events
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/events/healing/1

### Get Deaths
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/deaths/1

### Get Skill Timeline - All Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/skills/1

### Get Skill Timeline - Single Ability
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/skills/1?abilityID=12345

### Get Skill Timeline - Multiple Abilities
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/skills/1?abilityID=12345,67890,11111

### Get Skill Timeline - Specific Player
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/skills/1?sourceID=5

### Get Skill Timeline - Multiple Abilities from Specific Player
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/report/{{reportCode}}/skills/1?abilityID=12345,67890&sourceID=5

### Get Character Data
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/character/us/area-52/playerName

### Get Guild Data
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/guild/us/area-52/guildName

### Custom GraphQL Query - Simple
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "query { reportData { report(code: \"{{reportCode}}\") { title startTime endTime } } }"
}

### Custom GraphQL Query - With Variables
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "query GetReport($code: String!) { reportData { report(code: $code) { title fights { id name kill } } } }",
  "variables": {
    "code": "{{reportCode}}"
  }
}

### Custom GraphQL Query - Player Details
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "query { reportData { report(code: \"{{reportCode}}\") { masterData { actors(type: \"Player\") { id name type subType } } } } }"
}
